sentences: Saeko Ura (浦 彩恵子, Ura Saeko, born 1 April 1989, in Kagoshima Prefecture, Japan) is a Japanese singer.
She previously worked with the stage name Cherie.
She spent her high school and college years in Kansai.
Uura debuted her music career with the single "Tears: Namida wa Misetakunai" in the 27 December 2006.
In the 14 March 2007 she released the single "Sha la la –Ayakashi Night–", produced by B'z member Koshi Inaba, which became a hit.
In the 14 March 2007 she released the single "Sha la la –Ayakashi Night–", produced by B'z member Koshi Inaba, which became a hit.
In the 1 February 2011 she moved to Universal Music Japan and changed her name to Cherie.
She changed to her original name later in the 30 August 2012.
